2 WHEREAS, Roger Colbert served as President of the Greene-Clay Bar
3 Association and as a member of the House of Delegates of the Arkansas Bar
4 Association; and
5
6 WHEREAS, outside of his legal practice, Roger Colbert dedicated his
7 time to the development of Greene County through nonprofit organizations such
8 as the Community Foundation of Greene County and the Paragould Regional
9 Chamber of Commerce, where he served as Chairman of the Board in 2008; and
10
11 WHEREAS, Roger Colbert took immense pride in being named the Paragould
12 Chamber of Commerce Member of the Year in 2003 and the Greene County
13 Volunteer Attorney of the Year in 2011; and
14
15 WHEREAS, Roger Colbert was a lifelong fan of the St. Louis Cardinals
16 baseball team and rarely missed an opportunity to support his Arkansas State
17 Red Wolves in both basketball and football, and he also loved the University
18 of Missouri Tigers; and
19
20 WHEREAS, Roger Colbert is survived by his cherished daughters, Graycen
21 and Bailey, his devoted mother, Shelby, his siblings, Scott, Gina, and Lisa,
22 the mother of his daughters, Kelly, and his nephews; and
23
24 WHEREAS, Roger Colbert will be remembered and honored for his deep
25 commitment to family, his passion for the law, his love of sports, creating a
26 life well-lived, and harboring a spirit that will continue to resonate in the
27 lives he touched,
28
29 NOW THEREFORE,
30 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE NINETY-FIFTH GENERAL
31 ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
32
33 THAT the House of Representatives remember attorney Roger Colbert for
34 his contributions to the City of Paragould and Greene County, the Greene-Clay
35 Bar Association and the Arkansas Bar Association, and the State of Arkansas.
